to learn more,

00:32:43.600 --> 00:32:47.150
and realized that I
needed to learn more,

00:32:47.150 --> 00:32:52.790
to address better the issues
women are facing in my country.

00:32:52.790 --> 00:32:56.670
I therefore applied for--
and was granted-- a Fulbright

00:32:56.670 --> 00:33:00.520
scholarship to study at
the University of Oregon

00:33:00.520 --> 00:33:06.435
in gender, environment, and
environmental issues and women

00:33:06.435 --> 00:33:06.935
issues.

00:33:10.210 --> 00:33:13.890
So I first met InStove
during a stove demonstration

00:33:13.890 --> 00:33:16.140
at the University of Oregon.

00:33:16.140 --> 00:33:19.280
I immediately saw the
importance of the work

00:33:19.280 --> 00:33:22.270
on women, children,
and the planet.

00:33:22.270 --> 00:33:26.150
So, when I graduated
in the fall of 2013,

00:33:26.150 --> 00:33:29.840
