as Africa project coordinator,

00:33:29.840 --> 00:33:32.060
I immediately
accepted the offer.

00:33:35.850 --> 00:33:39.700
Unlike in the United States and
in most developed countries,

00:33:39.700 --> 00:33:43.500
the most common ways of cooking
in most African countries, even

00:33:43.500 --> 00:33:48.540
today, is cooking the food
over a three-stone fire,

00:33:48.540 --> 00:33:50.790
exactly as you see
in this picture,

00:33:50.790 --> 00:33:54.010
and as it's shown here.

00:33:54.010 --> 00:33:56.510
All generations
in my family have

00:33:56.510 --> 00:33:59.500
cooked the food over
a three-stone fire,

00:33:59.500 --> 00:34:02.510
including myself.

00:34:02.510 --> 00:34:05.770
One of my cousins
was severely burned

00:34:05.770 --> 00:34:10.540
when he was an infant, while my
aunt was holding him on her lap

00:34:10.540 --> 00:34:13.739
and stirring food from a pot.

00:34:13.739 --> 00:34:16.719
The [INAUDIBLE] pot
accidentally fell on him,

00:34:16.719 --> 00:34:19.300
and burned him badly.

00:34:19.300 --> 00:34:21.469
So he was disfigured.

00:34:21.469 --> 00:34:26.389
And he could no longer use his
left hand as a normal person.

00:34:26.389 --> 00:34:30.000
He's an adult now,
married with children.

00:34:30.000 --> 00:34:34.170
But he still has to
bear the consequences

00:34:34.170 --> 00:34:38.320
of the open-fire cooking method.

00:34:38.320 --> 00:34:41.100
Growing up, I've
seen my mom cook

00:34:41.100 --> 00:34:44.159
the food over a
three-stone fire.

00:34:44.159 --> 00:34:49.440
The walls of our kitchen back
home are all black from smoke.

00:34:49.440 --> 00:34:51.920
Traditionally,
being able to stand

00:34:51.920 --> 00:34:54.610
smoke while using
a three-stone fire

00:34:54.610 --> 00:34:58.960
is a rite of passage
for all girls.

00:34:58.960 --> 00:35:01.230
I remember once asking
my elder daughter,

00:35:01.230 --> 00:35:04.480
[? Fattouh, ?] to start
fire, because I needed

00:35:04.480 --> 00:35:06.880
to fix breakfast for the family.

00:35:06.880 --> 00:35:08.400
So she tried for hours.

00:35:08.400 --> 00:35:10.560
The fire wouldn't start.

00:35:10.560 --> 00:35:12.210
And her eyes were red.

00:35:12.210 --> 00:35:13.620
She was coughing.

00:35:13.620 --> 00:35:16.550
And our entire kitchen
was filled with smoke.

00:35:16.550 --> 00:35:19.810
And she kept telling me,
Mama, I can't start the fire.

00:35:19.810 --> 00:35:23.900
And I kept telling her that
she needed to try harder,

00:35:23.900 --> 00:35:27.890
because I thought she was just
being lazy, as all teenagers.

00:35:27.890 --> 00:35:31.720
So when I came to the
United States years later,

00:35:31.720 --> 00:35:36.120
I started taking classes
and learning new things that

00:35:36.120 --> 00:35:40.170
challenged the belief I
was told while growing up

00:35:40.170 --> 00:35:43.000
that all girls
needed to learn how

00:35:43.000 --> 00:35:45.720
to start a fire, no matter what.

00:35:45.720 --> 00:35:49.050
I realized that I was
too hard on my daughter.

00:35:49.050 --> 00:35:50.570
And I picked up
the phone one day.

00:35:50.570 --> 00:35:54.820
I called her to apologize
for being so hard on her.

00:35:54.820 --> 00:35:58.670
But I was trying-- I
was simply trying--

00:35:58.670 --> 00:36:01.730
to prepare her to
become a better woman,

00:36:01.730 --> 00:36:04.760
as I was taught
when I was a child.

00:36:14.180 --> 00:36:17.540
So cooking with a
three-stone fire method

00:36:17.540 --> 00:36:20.970
has a lot of
consequences on women,

00:36:20.970 --> 00:36:23.290
on people, and the environment.

00:36:23.290 --> 00:36:26.920
It leads to deforestation,
because the need is increasing,

00:36:26.920 --> 00:36:28.980
the demand is increasing.

00:36:28.980 --> 00:36:30.880
It also leads to
gender-based violence,

00:36:30.880 --> 00:36:33.290
because women have
to walk father

00:36:33.290 --> 00:36:37.605
in the bush to collect wood
for the needs of the family.

00:36:40.310 --> 00:36:44.300
So open-fire cooking
also contributes

00:36:44.300 --> 00:36:49.330
to lots of diseases, like
eyes, lungs, and heart disease.

00:36:49.330 --> 00:36:51.270
I have two of my
daughters who have

00:36:51.270 --> 00:36:55.930
been diagnosed with
asthma, from smoke.

00:36:55.930 --> 00:36:59.270
Open-fire cooking
contributes also to burns,

00:36:59.270 --> 00:37:01.900
as was the case with my
little cousin, Mamadou,

00:37:01.900 --> 00:37:05.790
when he was an infant.

00:37:05.790 --> 00:37:09.030
It's also a big loss
of time for families.

00:37:09.030 --> 00:37:12.050
Because it takes hours
to just set the fire.

00:37:12.050 --> 00:37:14.080
And because it's not efficient.

00:37:14.080 --> 00:37:17.770
Most fire does not go directly
to the pot, because it's open.

00:37:17.770 --> 00:37:19.630
And it takes a lot of time.

00:37:19.630 --> 00:37:22.410
And women could use
this time to carry out

00:37:22.410 --> 00:37:25.057
other income-generating
activities

00:37:25.057 --> 00:37:26.140
to support their families.

00:37:34.490 --> 00:37:38.890
So today, as an African
woman, and a mom

00:37:38.890 --> 00:37:41.970
who has lived all these
things InStove has been trying

00:37:41.970 --> 00:37:46.220
to address, I think that
it is unacceptable today,

00:37:46.220 --> 00:37:49.720
in this age of
high-technology development,

00:37:49.720 --> 00:37:52.920
for women and girls
to continue to suffer,

00:37:52.920 --> 00:37:56.602
to expose their lives to
danger, and harm their health,

00:37:56.602 --> 00:37:58.435
just because they want
to feed their family.

00:38:03.690 --> 00:38:06.170
But it does not have
to be like that.

00:38:06.170 --> 00:38:10.220
Because there is an alternative
to the three-stone cooking

00:38:10.220 --> 00:38:11.770
fire method.

00:38:11.770 --> 00:38:14.480
InStove cook stove is here.

00:38:14.480 --> 00:38:18.220
It's safe, very fast,
efficient, because it does not

00:38:18.220 --> 00:38:20.550
use a lot of the wood.

00:38:20.550 --> 00:38:22.040
And they do not
produce any smoke.

00:38:31.670 --> 00:38:35.190
So, in this picture, you can
